of short GRBs occur at z {\textgreater}{\~{}} 2 and have fainter afterglows due to their higher redshifts. The high-redshift scenario leads to a bimodal redshift distribution, with peaks at z {\~{}} 0.5 and z {\~{}} 3. The large offset scenario leads to an offset distribution that is well matched by theoretical predictions of NS-NS/NS-BH binary kicks, or by a hybrid population with globular cluster NS-NS binaries at large offsets and primordial binaries at offsets of lsim10 kpc (indicative of negligible kicks). Deeper constraints on any coincident galaxies to gsim28 mag (using the Hubble Space Telescope) will allow us to better exclude the high-redshift scenario.},
